// step_bucketsInfo.pug

div#buckets-info-step
  div.buckets-guide-container
    h2 📄 Get Your Spreadsheet Ready
  
    p Before importing your Buckets Report data, make sure your spreadsheet has these columns:
  
    ol.guide-steps
      li
        span.step-icon 1️⃣
        span.step-text 
          strong Client ID (Optional unless uploading new accounts)
          |  – A unique ID for each client
      li
        span.step-icon 2️⃣
        span.step-text 
          strong Account Number
          |  – The account tied to the client
      li
        span.step-icon 3️⃣
        span.step-text 
          strong Withdraw Amount
          |  – The dollar amount withdrawn regularly
      li
        span.step-icon 4️⃣
        span.step-text 
          strong Withdraw Frequency
          |  – e.g., Monthly, Quarterly, Annually
      li
        span.step-icon 5️⃣
        span.step-text 
          strong Asset Allocation:
          ul.asset-list
            li 💰 Cash %
            li 🏠 Income %
            li 🛡️ Annuities %
            li 📈 Growth %
          p.note-text These should all add up to 100% for each account.

    p.mt-3
      | • All fields are required for a full and accurate Buckets report. 
      br
      | • Source data from any CRM, or start with our template below.

    a.import-action-item.d-block.mt-2(
      href='/downloads/buckets-account-import-template.xlsx'
      download
    )
      i.fas.fa-file-download.me-1
      | Download the Buckets Import template
    a.import-action-item.learn-more-btn.d-block.mt-2(
      href='#'
      data-video-id='76979871'
      data-bs-toggle='modal'
      data-bs-target='#learnMoreVideoModal'
    )
      i.fas.fa-play-circle.me-1
      | Watch an instructional video (2 min)
  
    .example-header
      h4 🧪 Example Header Row:
      code Client ID | Account Number | Withdraw Amount | Withdraw Frequency | Cash % | Income % | Annuities % | Growth %
  
